         <abstract>
            <p>The convergence of product integration rules, based on Gaussian quadrature points, is investigated for functions with interior and endpoint singularities over bounded and unbounded intervals. The investigation is based on a new convergence result for Lagrangian interpolation and Gaussian quadrature of singular integrands.</p>
          </abstract>
